# Vibe Coding Rules

- Use `clsx(...)` for every JSX `className` value (including single static classes).
- In `clsx(...)`, pass classes as separate comma-separated string arguments (for example `clsx("flex", "items-center")`, not `clsx("flex items-center")`).
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over bespoke component CSS when practical.
- Keep Tailwind classes automatically sorted through the shared Prettier config.
- When adding class helper wrappers, prefer `clsx` and keep naming simple (`cn` only when needed).
- Keep components small and composable; extract repeated UI blocks.
- Do not use inline styles (`style={{ ... }}`) in JSX.
- Do not use arbitrary Tailwind values (for example `w-[232px]`, `tracking-[0.2em]`).
- If arbitrary styling is required, create a sibling component stylesheet named after the component (for example `our-component.css`).
- Component stylesheets must use strict BEM with every class prefixed by the component name block (for example `our-component__...`).
- React linting baseline uses `@eslint-react/eslint-plugin`; do not add `eslint-plugin-react` back unless explicitly requested.
- Use kebab-case for filenames by default.
- Keep framework-required filenames as-is (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `route.ts`, `robots.ts`, etc.).
- Use arrow functions wherever possible.
- Use hoisted `function` declarations only when explicitly necessary.
- Do not reference the React UMD global (for example `React.ReactNode`); import types from `react` instead (for example `import type { ReactNode } from "react";`).
